@prefix : <https://www.somusicvocabulary.org/music#> .
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

# NEGATIVE: :MusicalRoleShape — :hasRole must point at a :MusicalRole, not at any old node.
#
# The role vocabulary is now DATA (gist:Category individuals in the ABox) rather than schema,
# which is the point — a new role is one triple, not a TBox release. The price is that nothing
# in the class hierarchy constrains what may sit on the object end any more, so SHACL has to.
# Without this, `:SomeAgent :hasRole :Guitar` is a perfectly good triple.

:NEG_RoleConfusedPerson a :MusicalPerson ;
    rdfs:label "Negative fixture — holds a guitar as though it were a role"@en ;
    :hasRole :NEG_NotARole ;
    .

:NEG_NotARole a :MusicalInstrument ;
    rdfs:label "Negative fixture — an instrument, not a role"@en ;
    .
